Notice No. 00-398

November 17, 2000


TO:

ALL NYMEX/COMEX DIVISION MEMBERS AND MEMBER FIRMS

ALL NYMEX/COMEX DIVISION CLEARING FIRMS

ALL NYMEX/COMEX DIVISION OPERATIONS MANAGERS


FROM: Neal Wolkoff, Executive Vice President


RE: NYMEX Rule 9.33/COMEX Rule 4.46 ) Large Trader Position Reporting For

Thanksgiving Day Holiday

___________________________________________________________


This is a reminder that the New York Mercantile Exchange ("the "Exchange")

and its COMEX Division will be closed on Thursday, November 23 and Friday,

November 24, 2000.  The Compliance Department,s modem lines can accept

NYMEX/COMEX large trader data transmissions for the close of business

Wednesday, November 22, 2000, any time after 8:00 P.M. on Wednesday, November

22 until 8:00 A.M. on Monday, November 27, 2000.


 If your large trader data for the trade date November 22, 2000 is

transmitted on any day other than Thursday, November 23, 2000, please ensure

that the trade date that appears in each record is November 22, 2000.  The

computer system will accept no other date.  There have been problems in the

past when the Exchange was closed because clearing members, computer systems

automatically counted ahead one day.  In such cases, the data transmitted on

the first business day following the Exchange holiday incorrectly referenced

the trade date as the date of the holiday instead of the date preceding it.


Should you have any questions, please contact Bonnie H. Yurga at (212)

299-2879, or Nick Falcone at (212) 299-2919.


